name: ChannelMediaRelayError
description: The error code of the channel media replay.

parameters.ServerErrorResponse: 1: An error occurs in the server response.

parameters.ServerNoResponse:
2: No server response.
      You can call leaveChannel to leave the channel.
      This error can also occur if your project has not enabled co-host token authentication. Contact support@agora.io to enable the co-host token authentication service before starting a channel media relay.

parameters.NoResourceAvailable: 3: The SDK fails to access the service, probably due to limited resources of the server.

parameters.FailedJoinSourceChannel: 4: Fails to send the relay request.

parameters.FailedJoinDestinationChannel: 5: Fails to accept the relay request.

parameters.FailedPacketReceivedFromSource: 6: The server fails to receive the media stream.

parameters.FailedPacketSentToDestination: 7: The server fails to send the media stream.

parameters.ServerConnectionLost: 8: The SDK disconnects from the server due to poor network connections. You can call the leaveChannel method to leave the channel.

parameters.InternalError: 9: An internal error occurs in the server.

parameters.SourceTokenExpired: 10: The token of the source channel has expired.

parameters.DestinationTokenExpired: 11: The token of the destination channel has expired.
